SFC analysis is a graph theory metric that detects both direct and indirect functional couplings between a predefined seed region and other brain regions (Fig. 1B)16,68,69. SFC analysis aims to characterize regions connected to specific seed brain areas at different levels of link-step distances16,68,69. With such a framework, a step refers to the number of links (edges) that belong to a path connecting a node to the seed (or target) area. In SFC analysis, the degree of stepwise connectivity of a voxel j for a given step distance l and a seed area i (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
